-- U.A.E. Interrogates Suspects on State Security Threats, WAM Says
-- B y   D a h l i a   K h o l a i f
-- 2012-07-15T15:01:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-15/u-a-e-interrogates-suspects-on-state-security-threats-wam-says.html
The United Arab Emirates public
prosecutor is investigating a group of suspects accused of
forming and managing an organization to conduct “crimes against
state security and the constitution,” the WAM state news
service said  on its website , citing the prosecutor.  The defendants, who are also charged with jeopardizing
“the main principles underlying the rule in the state” and for
having ties with “foreign agendas and organizations,” were
detained and are in custody pending investigation, said Salem
Saeed, the public prosecutor, according to the news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dahlia Kholaif in Kuwait at 
 dkholaif@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
